node.text:
You become what you constantly feed your mind with.

If you constantly feed your mind with, “I can’t afford that, I can’t be rich, I can’t do that...”

Well guess what, you’re right.

Instead of telling yourself statements, which only closes the mind.

Change it to: “HOW can I afford that?”, “How can I be rich?”, “How can I do that?”. 

This will broaden your mind and you will start to think of solutions to your problem rather than excuses.

Did you find this helpful? Follow @savetoinvest for more!

#robertkiyosaki #moneymindset #richmindset #richmind #mindsetshift #changeyourmindset #savetoinvest

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Money | Business | Finance on September 20, 2021 tagging @thewealthdad. May be an image of text that says 'The Wealth Dad @thewealthdad That 3% raise you got last year on your $60,000 salary put your new salary at $61,800. But thanks to inflation (5.3% YoY) that $61,800 "increased" salary is actually only worth $58,525 in purchasing power today If your money isn't growing> inflation, you're losing money.'.

node.text:
If you didn't get a 6% salary increase this year, you essentially got a pay cut. Fiat money is constantly losing its purchasing power, and the tricky part is that most of the time it goes unnoticed.

The first step to stay on top of inflation is to become aware of it, and secondly, you must take action by putting your money into assets that will outgrow it. 📈

(Some examples: Index funds, ETFs, rental properties, individual stocks, crypto, etc...)

node.text:
